  "text": "Analyzing the 12 spots that match with a-or b-tubulin showing a variation in phosphorylation levels in response to incubation of trypomastigotes with fibronectin or laminin (Tables S1 and S2), it was found that all a-and b-tubulin spots analyzed have very significant score numbers, percentage of coverage and number of peptides sequenced, indicating a very successful protein identification. In general, adhesion of trypomastigotes to fibronectin leads to a strong dephosphorylation of a-tubulin (spots 37, 44, 64), and b-tubulin 1.9 (spot 58), as summarized in Table 1 . It should be noted that isoform b-tubulin 1.9 (Q8STF3), which differs from btubulin (P08562) by 4 residues (S 274 , D 288 , L 289 and A 306 changed by the amino acids T, E, V, R in b-Tubulin 1.9, respectively), was described in other proteomic analysis of T. cruzi [CITATION_1] .",
